@abergeron requires this feature for Myia.

@slyubomirsky check out this example, I wrote up a small function to do so in Python. 

https://gist.github.com/jroesch/4f6a601cbc86170025011d9d34a708dc

Some additional comments: The pass interface can be minimized into the following items:

- ResolveDependency can be simply internal to SequentialPass, which and get called when we create a Sequential pass
- CreatePass do not need to be a virtual function, we can have CreateFunctionPass and CreateSequentialPass as global functions.

A mock proposal

```c++
class PassNode : public RelayNode {
  public:
   std::string name;
   int opt_level;
   // enabled should not be the member of the passcode, instead should be the member of the SequentialPass
   // Use virtual function, the data structure can reside in the child class.
   virtual std::vector<std::string> Required() const = 0;
   virtual void SetContext(const PassContext&) = 0; 
   virtual Module operator()(const Module& mod) = 0;
};
```

Let us use the ir_pass namespace

@tqchen I'm having some weird problems with includes.  Maybe my approach is wrong, but I'm trying to take the functions from `nnvm/src/compiler/graph_runtime.cc` and put them in `src/runtime/graph/graph_runtime.cc`.  These functions require the following node to be defined in the header:
```c++
/*!
 * \brief wrapper node container for exchange.
 */
struct NDArrayWrapperNode : public ::tvm::Node {
  std::string name;
  tvm::runtime::NDArray array;

  void VisitAttrs(tvm::AttrVisitor* v) final {
    v->Visit("name", &name);
    v->Visit("array", &array);
  }

  static constexpr const char* _type_key = "NDArrayWrapper";
  TVM_DECLARE_NODE_TYPE_INFO(NDArrayWrapperNode, Node);
};

TVM_DEFINE_NODE_REF(NDArrayWrapper, NDArrayWrapperNode);
```
.  But when I try to put `#include <tvm/node/node.h>` in the header, it says it can't find that header.

Is there a different header I should be including, or is this struct definition using outdated types?
